    surveyRepository.findAll(PageRequest.of(0,10))

returns a `Page&lt;T&gt;` (provided your `surveyRepository` is a default [PagingAndSortingRepository][1])

This `Page` neither implements `Collection` nor `Map` and it isn&#39;t an array. But it implements `Iterable` so thymeleaf will compute the size as `null`. You can check the relevant code [here][2].

What you could do is instead of passing the `Page` to the model pass a `Collection` instead:

    @GetMapping(path = &quot;/&quot;)
    public String homePage(Model model) {
        List&lt;Survey&gt; surveys = surveyRepository.findAll(PageRequest.of(0,10)).getContent();
        model.addAttribute(&quot;surveys&quot;, surveys);
        return &quot;index&quot;;
    }


  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-data/data-commons/docs/current/api/org/springframework/data/repository/PagingAndSortingRepository.html
  [2]: https://github.com/thymeleaf/thymeleaf/blob/e5434ee1dc5145c8a2a5ff50a40bffa16c63a412/lib/thymeleaf/src/main/java/org/thymeleaf/engine/IteratedGatheringModelProcessable.java#L410

